He will continue to dole out oil-based subsidies in the well-worn Venezuelan tradition of Marcos PÃ©rez JimÃ©nez and Carlos AndrÃ©s PÃ©rez.
As a result, ChÃ¡vez will be re-elected late next year, and he may well remain in power until the end of the next decade.
Yet, if this is what the Venezuelan people want, then so be it.
